Hot Telecommunication System Ltd. (HOT) 
headed for the highest close in almost three weeks after the
board approved a plan to buy back as much as 184 million shekels
($47 million) of stock last week.  Shares of Israelâ€™s second-largest fixed-line operator
advanced 2.2 percent to 35.53 shekels, poised for the highest
level since May 14, at 12.46 p.m. in Tel Aviv. The stock has
rallied 9.1 percent in the past two trading days. The benchmark
TA-25 index declined 2.2 percent.  Hot, which started offering mobile-phone services last
month, said on May 31 the company plans to acquire about 3.2
